{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":836,"text":"Some people are obsessed\nby French wines."},{"time":4302,"text":"Others love playing golf"},{"time":6548,"text":"or devouring literature."},{"time":8729,"text":"One of my greatest pleasures\nin life is, I have to admit,"},{"time":12328,"text":"a bit special."},{"time":13946,"text":"I cannot tell you how much I enjoy\nwatching cities from the sky,"},{"time":18938,"text":"from an airplane window."}]},{"cues":[{"time":20916,"text":"Some cities are calmly industrious,"},{"time":23935,"text":"like Dusseldorf"},{"time":25499,"text":"or Louisville."},{"time":27780,"text":"Others project an energy\nthat they can hardly contain,"},{"time":31437,"text":"like New York"},{"time":32778,"text":"or Hong Kong."},{"time":34524,"text":"And then you have Paris"},{"time":37492,"text":"or Istanbul,"},{"time":39228,"text":"and their patina full of history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42108,"text":"I see cities as living beings."},{"time":44514,"text":"And when I discover them from far above,"},{"time":47006,"text":"I like to find those main streets\nand highways that structure their space."},{"time":52019,"text":"Especially at night,"},{"time":53519,"text":"when commuters make these arteries\nlook dramatically red and golden:"},{"time":58908,"text":"the city's vascular system\nperforming its vital function"},{"time":63219,"text":"right before your eyes."},{"time":65569,"text":"But when I'm sitting in my car"},{"time":69020,"text":"after an hour and a half\nof commute every day,"},{"time":72336,"text":"that reality looks very different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74237,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":75315,"text":"Nothing --"},{"time":76497,"text":"not public radio,"},{"time":78211,"text":"no podcast --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":79394,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":80446,"text":"Not even mindfulness meditation"},{"time":82479,"text":"makes this time worth living."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84118,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":86072,"text":"Isn't it absurd"},{"time":87250,"text":"that we created cars\nthat can reach 130 miles per hour"},{"time":91731,"text":"and we now drive them at the same speed\nas 19th-century horse carriages?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":97377,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":98660,"text":"In the US alone,"},{"time":100426,"text":"we spent 29.6 billion hours\ncommuting in 2014."},{"time":106281,"text":"With that amount of time,"},{"time":107923,"text":"ancient Egyptians could have built\n26 Pyramids of Giza."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112238,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":113308,"text":"We do that in one year."},{"time":114730,"text":"A monumental waste of time,\nenergy and human potential."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120154,"text":"For decades,"},{"time":121355,"text":"our remedy for congestion was simple:"},{"time":123687,"text":"build new roads or enlarge existing ones."},{"time":127198,"text":"And it worked."},{"time":128372,"text":"It worked admirably for Paris,"},{"time":130854,"text":"when the city tore down\nhundreds of historical buildings"},{"time":133968,"text":"to create 85 miles"},{"time":135639,"text":"of transportation-friendly boulevards."},{"time":138879,"text":"And it still works today\nin fast-growing emerging cities."},{"time":142549,"text":"But in more established urban centers,"},{"time":144969,"text":"significant network expansions\nare almost impossible:"},{"time":148923,"text":"habitat is just too dense,"},{"time":150867,"text":"real estate, too expensive"},{"time":152864,"text":"and public finances, too fragile."},{"time":155780,"text":"Our city's vascular system\nis getting clogged, it's getting sick,"},{"time":159409,"text":"and we should pay attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161040,"text":"Our current way\nof thinking is not working."},{"time":164172,"text":"For our transportation to flow,"},{"time":166117,"text":"we need a new source of inspiration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170187,"text":"So after 16 years\nworking in transportation,"},{"time":173437,"text":"my \"aha moment\" happened\nwhen speaking with a biotech customer."},{"time":177622,"text":"She was telling me how her treatment"},{"time":179674,"text":"was leveraging specific properties\nof our vascular system."},{"time":183582,"text":"\"Wow,\" I thought, \"Our vascular system --"},{"time":186074,"text":"all the veins and arteries in our body"},{"time":189174,"text":"making miracles of logistics every day.\""},{"time":193112,"text":"This is the moment I realized"},{"time":195294,"text":"that biology has been\nin the transportation business"},{"time":198301,"text":"for billions of years."},{"time":200364,"text":"It has been testing countless solutions"},{"time":202752,"text":"to move nutrients, gases and proteins."},{"time":206532,"text":"It really is the world's most\nsophisticated transportation laboratory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211326,"text":"So, what if the solution to our traffic\nchallenges was inside us?"},{"time":217895,"text":"I wanted to know:"},{"time":219184,"text":"Why is it that blood flows\nin our veins most of our lives,"},{"time":223004,"text":"when our big cities get clogged\non a daily basis?"},{"time":226990,"text":"And the reality is that you're looking\nat two very different networks."},{"time":232013,"text":"I don't know if you realize,"},{"time":234223,"text":"but each of us has 60,000 miles\nof blood vessels in our bodies --"},{"time":238944,"text":"60,000 miles."},{"time":240262,"text":"That's two-and-a-half times\nthe Earth's circumference,"},{"time":242878,"text":"inside you."},{"time":244860,"text":"What it means is that blood vessels\nare everywhere inside us,"},{"time":248203,"text":"not just under the surface of our skin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250610,"text":"But if you look at our cities,"},{"time":252843,"text":"yes, we have some\nunderground subway systems"},{"time":255965,"text":"and some tunnels and bridges,"},{"time":258405,"text":"and also some helicopters in the sky."},{"time":260709,"text":"But the vast majority of our traffic\nis focused on the ground,"},{"time":264792,"text":"on the surface."},{"time":266450,"text":"So in other words,"},{"time":267829,"text":"while our vascular system uses\nthe three dimensions inside us,"},{"time":272232,"text":"our urban transportation\nis mostly two-dimensional."},{"time":275881,"text":"And so what we need\nis to embrace that verticality."},{"time":279290,"text":"If our surface grid is saturated,"},{"time":281879,"text":"well, let's elevate our traffic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284174,"text":"This Chinese concept of a bus\nthat can straddle traffic jams --"},{"time":288694,"text":"that was an eye-opener on new ways\nto think about space and movement"},{"time":293103,"text":"inside our cities."},{"time":294863,"text":"And we can go higher,"},{"time":296699,"text":"and suspend our transportation\nlike we did with our electrical grid."},{"time":301968,"text":"Tel Aviv and Abu Dhabi\nare talking about testing"},{"time":305009,"text":"these futuristic networks\nof suspended magnetic pods."},{"time":309465,"text":"And we can keep climbing, and fly."},{"time":313263,"text":"The fact that a company like Airbus"},{"time":315214,"text":"is now seriously working\non flying urban taxis"},{"time":318546,"text":"is telling us something."},{"time":320633,"text":"Flying cars are finally moving\nfrom science-fiction déjà vu"},{"time":325525,"text":"to attractive business-case territory."},{"time":328238,"text":"And that's an exciting moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330415,"text":"So building this 3-D\ntransportation network"},{"time":333068,"text":"is one of the ways we can mitigate\nand solve traffic jams."},{"time":338410,"text":"But it's not the only one."},{"time":340257,"text":"We have to question"},{"time":341899,"text":"other fundamental choices\nthat we made, like the vehicles we use."},{"time":346278,"text":"Just imagine a very familiar scene:"},{"time":348983,"text":"You've been driving for 42 minutes."},{"time":351656,"text":"The two kids behind you\nare getting restless."},{"time":354899,"text":"And you're late."},{"time":356754,"text":"Do you see that slow car in front of you?"},{"time":359474,"text":"Always comes when you're late, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":361316,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":362475,"text":"That driver is looking for parking."},{"time":365193,"text":"There is no parking spot\navailable in the area,"},{"time":367434,"text":"but how would he know?"},{"time":369552,"text":"It is estimated that up to 30 percent\nof urban traffic is generated"},{"time":374492,"text":"by drivers looking for parking."},{"time":377091,"text":"Do you see the 100 cars around you?"},{"time":379549,"text":"Eighty-five of them\nonly have one passenger."},{"time":382571,"text":"Those 85 drivers could all fit\nin one Londonian red bus."},{"time":387339,"text":"So the question is:"},{"time":388514,"text":"Why are we wasting so much space\nif it is what we need the most?"},{"time":391598,"text":"Why are we doing this to ourselves?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":393746,"text":"Biology would never do this."},{"time":396189,"text":"Space inside our arteries\nis fully utilized."},{"time":399722,"text":"At every heartbeat,"},{"time":401270,"text":"a higher blood pressure literally compacts\nmillions of red blood cells"},{"time":405307,"text":"into massive trains of oxygen"},{"time":407449,"text":"that quickly flow throughout our body."},{"time":409771,"text":"And the tiny space inside our red\nblood cells is not wasted, either."},{"time":414357,"text":"In healthy conditions,"},{"time":416098,"text":"more than 95 percent\nof their oxygen capacity is utilized."},{"time":420494,"text":"Can you imagine if the vehicles\nwe used in our cities"},{"time":423379,"text":"were 95 percent full,"},{"time":425087,"text":"all the additional space\nyou would have to walk, to bike"},{"time":428495,"text":"and to enjoy our cities?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":430616,"text":"The reason blood is so\nincredibly efficient"},{"time":434153,"text":"is that our red blood cells\nare not dedicated"},{"time":437278,"text":"to specific organs or tissues;"},{"time":439497,"text":"otherwise, we would probably have\ntraffic jams in our veins."},{"time":442632,"text":"No, they're shared."},{"time":443888,"text":"They're shared by all\nthe cells of our body."},{"time":446737,"text":"And because our network is so extensive,"},{"time":449414,"text":"each one of our 37 trillion cells\ngets its own deliveries of oxygen"},{"time":454198,"text":"precisely when it needs them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456253,"text":"Blood is both a collective\nand individual form of transportation."},{"time":461513,"text":"But for our cities,"},{"time":463081,"text":"we've been stuck."},{"time":464389,"text":"We've been stuck in an endless debate"},{"time":466458,"text":"between creating a car-centric society\nor extensive mass-transit systems."},{"time":472295,"text":"I think we should transcend this."},{"time":473934,"text":"I think we can create vehicles\nthat combine the convenience of cars"},{"time":478277,"text":"and the efficiencies of trains and buses."},{"time":481459,"text":"Just imagine."},{"time":482888,"text":"You're comfortably sitting\nin a fast and smooth urban train,"},{"time":487160,"text":"along with 1,200 passengers."},{"time":489950,"text":"The problem with urban trains"},{"time":491661,"text":"is that sometimes you have to stop\nfive, ten, fifteen times"},{"time":496080,"text":"before your final destination."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498421,"text":"What if in this train\nyou didn't have to stop?"},{"time":501929,"text":"In this train,"},{"time":503222,"text":"wagons can detach dynamically\nwhile you're moving"},{"time":507012,"text":"and become express, driverless buses"},{"time":509518,"text":"that move on a secondary road network."},{"time":512024,"text":"And so without a single stop,"},{"time":513949,"text":"nor a lengthy transfer,"},{"time":515560,"text":"you are now sitting in a bus\nthat is headed toward your suburb."},{"time":519647,"text":"And when you get close,"},{"time":521597,"text":"the section you're sitting in detaches"},{"time":524928,"text":"and self-drives you\nright to your doorstep."},{"time":528523,"text":"It is collective and individual\nat the same time."},{"time":531922,"text":"This could be one of the shared,\nmodular, driverless vehicles of tomorrow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":537681,"text":"Now ..."},{"time":539217,"text":"as if walking in a city\nbuzzing with drones,"},{"time":542399,"text":"flying taxis, modular buses\nand suspended magnetic pods"},{"time":546710,"text":"was not exotic enough,"},{"time":549062,"text":"I think there is another force in action"},{"time":551023,"text":"that will make urban traffic mesmerizing."},{"time":554541,"text":"If you think about it,"},{"time":556154,"text":"the current generation of driverless cars\nis just trying to earn its way"},{"time":561184,"text":"into a traffic grid\nmade by and for humans."},{"time":564626,"text":"They're trying to learn traffic rules,\nwhich is relatively simple,"},{"time":568551,"text":"and coping with human unpredictability,"},{"time":570484,"text":"which is more challenging."}]},{"cues":[{"time":573063,"text":"But what would happen\nwhen whole cities become driverless?"},{"time":576999,"text":"Would we need traffic lights?"},{"time":578851,"text":"Would we need lanes?"},{"time":580471,"text":"How about speed limits?"},{"time":582563,"text":"Red blood cells are not flowing in lanes."},{"time":585402,"text":"They never stop at red lights."},{"time":587387,"text":"In the first driverless cities,"},{"time":589387,"text":"you would have no red lights and no lanes."},{"time":592014,"text":"And when all the cars\nare driverless and connected,"},{"time":595630,"text":"everything is predictable\nand reaction time, minimum."},{"time":599219,"text":"They can drive much faster"},{"time":601157,"text":"and can take any rational initiative\nthat can speed them up"},{"time":604118,"text":"or the cars around them."},{"time":606600,"text":"So instead of rigid traffic rules,"},{"time":610203,"text":"flow will be regulated"},{"time":611559,"text":"by a mesh of dynamic and constantly\nself-improving algorithms."},{"time":618468,"text":"The result: a strange traffic"},{"time":621219,"text":"that mixes the fast and smooth\nrigor of German autobahns"},{"time":624754,"text":"and the creative vitality\nof the intersections of Mumbai."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628695,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":630278,"text":"Traffic will be functionally exuberant."},{"time":632257,"text":"It will be liquid like our blood."},{"time":634722,"text":"And by a strange paradox,"},{"time":636502,"text":"the more robotized\nour traffic grid will be,"},{"time":639337,"text":"the more organic and alive\nits movement will feel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643075,"text":"So yes,"},{"time":644876,"text":"biology has all the attributes\nof a transportation genius today."},{"time":648598,"text":"But this process has taken\nbillions of years,"},{"time":651431,"text":"and went through all sorts\nof iterations and mutations."},{"time":654892,"text":"We can't wait billions of years\nto evolve our transportation system."},{"time":658979,"text":"We now have the dreams,"},{"time":660831,"text":"the concepts"},{"time":662147,"text":"and the technology"},{"time":664477,"text":"to create 3-D transportation networks,"},{"time":667351,"text":"invent new vehicles"},{"time":669090,"text":"and change the flow in our cities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671109,"text":"Let's do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":672288,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":673476,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}